def iso_week(dataframe, col=0,year=2015,month=7,day=1):
    ''' 
    Convert in iso week creating a new column called "Date iso week" and sum views in the same iso week.
    Create also a new column with year
    col: data column, def=0
    year= starting year, def=2015
    month= starting month, def=7
    day=starting day, def=1
    '''
    
    dt = datetime.date(year,month,day)
    wk = dt.isocalendar()[1]
    dataframe['Date iso week']=pd.to_datetime(dataframe.iloc[:,col]).dt.strftime('%Y-%V')
    
    #sum views of the same iso week
    sum_iso_week=dataframe.groupby("Date iso week").sum()
    sum_iso_week=sum_iso_week.reset_index()
    
    #for the sak of simplicity add a column with year
    year=[]
    for i in sum_iso_week['Date iso week']:
        year.append(i[:4])
    sum_iso_week['year']=year   
    
    return sum_iso_week

def data_years(dataframe, year):
    '''
    Create a new data frame only for the inserted year
    '''
    year=str(year)
    dataframe=dataframe.loc[(dataframe["year"]==year)]
    
    return dataframe

def plot(dataframe,label2,label1="Date iso week", title=1,typ=0,model_name=None):
    '''
    Plot dataframes and calculate Pearson correlation
    '''
    if typ==0:
        label2=str(label2)
    
        plt.figure(figsize=(14,6))
        sns.set_style("darkgrid")

        plt.plot('Date iso week', label2, data=dataframe)
        ax=plt.subplot()
        loc = plticker.MultipleLocator(base=8.0) # this locator puts ticks at regular intervals
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(loc)
        plt.xticks(fontsize=13,rotation=50)
        if title==1:
            plt.title("Wikipedia "+ label2 + " trend",fontsize=15)
        else:
            plt.title("Influnet Trend",fontsize=15)
        
        plt.show()
        corre= None
            
    if typ==1:
        
        sns.set_style("darkgrid")
        
        dataframe.plot(x='Date iso week', y=label2, figsize=(14,6))
        ax=plt.subplot()
        
        plt.xticks(fontsize=12,rotation=50)
        plt.title("%s vs %s" %(label2[0],label2[1]))
        plt.show()
        corre=dataframe.corr(method="pearson")["Incidenza totale"][2]
        print("Pearson Correlation: \n",dataframe.corr(method="pearson"))
    
    if typ==2:
        
        sns.set_style("darkgrid")
        
        dataframe.plot(x='Date iso week', y=label2, figsize=(14,6))
        ax=plt.subplot()
        
        plt.xticks(fontsize=12,rotation=50)
        plt.title("%s vs %s" %(label2[0],label2[1]))
        
        plt.show()
        print("Pearson Correlation: \n",dataframe.corr(method="pearson"))
        corre=None
    
    if typ==3:
        
        sns.set_style("darkgrid")
        
        dataframe.plot(x='Date iso week', y=label2, figsize=(14,6))
        ax=plt.subplot()
        
        plt.xticks(fontsize=12,rotation=50)
        plt.title("%s vs multi" %(label2[0]))
        plt.show()
        corre=None
        
    if typ==4:
        
        sns.set_style("darkgrid")
        
        dataframe.plot(x='Date iso week', y=label2, figsize=(14,6))

def influnet(file_name, ext=".txt",sep=" ",level1="level_0",level2="level_4"):
    '''
    Open influnet files, and save just the used colums (1 and 5), convert "," in "." and convert str to num
    file_name= "file name" or "complete path"
    ext="extension", def=".txt"
    sep=separator, def= " "
    
    '''
    path=str(file_name)
    ext=str(ext)
    path=path+ext
    influ=pd.read_csv(path, sep=sep)
    influ=influ.reset_index()
    influ=influ[[level1,level2]]
    influ.columns=["Date iso week","Incidenza totale"]
    influ["Incidenza totale"]=influ["Incidenza totale"].str.replace(",",".")
    influ["Incidenza totale"]=pd.to_numeric(influ["Incidenza totale"])
    influ.reset_index(inplace=True)
    influ.drop("index", axis=1, inplace=True)

    return influ

def normalize(dataframe,col):
    """
    Standardize dataframe's columns
    col format: ["col_name_1","col_name_2"]
    """
    scaler = MinMaxScaler()
    dataframe[col]=scaler.fit_transform(dataframe[col])
    
    dataframe=dataframe.iloc[1:]
    
    return dataframe

def model_analysis(model,X,y,date, model_name=None, plots=True):
    '''
    plots = False by default: plot original data and predicted data
    Training set and Test set are created, Training size = 0.67, Test size= 0.33; fixed random state = 2
    This function return the predicted values and a dataframe with error values
    
    '''
    
    if model == 1:
        model = LinearRegression()
        model_name="Linear Regression"
    if model == 2:
        model = Ridge(alpha=0.001)
        model_name = "Ridge"
    if model == 3:
        model = Lasso(alpha=0.000001)
        model_name = "Lasso"
    if model == 4:
        model = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=1000, random_state=1)
        model_name = "Random Forest"
    if model == 5:
        model = GradientBoostingRegressor(learning_rate = .07, n_estimators = 500, random_state=2)
        model_name = "Gradient Boosting"
    if model ==6:
        model=kernel_ridge.KernelRidge(alpha=0.001, kernel="rbf", gamma=0.5)
        model_name= "Kernel Ridge"
        
        
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.33, random_state=1)
    model.fit(X_train,y_train)
    
    y_pred=model.predict(X_test)
    
    pred= model.predict(X)
    data = pd.DataFrame({"Actual": y, "Pred": pred})
    df=pd.concat([data,date], axis=1, join='inner')
    
    mae_t=mean_absolute_error(y_test,y_pred)
    mae=mean_absolute_error(y,pred)

    
    if plots == True:
        plot(df,label2=["Actual","Pred"],typ=4, model_name=model_name)
        print("R2 Test: ",metrics.r2_score(y_test,y_pred))
        print("RMSE Test: ",np.sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test,y_pred)))
        print("R2 Total: ",metrics.r2_score(y,pred))
        print("RMSE Total: ",np.sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(y,pred)))
        print("Test Mean Absolute Error: ",mae_t)
        print("Total Mean Absolute Error: ",mae)
    
    d = {"Model":[model_name],'R2 Test': [metrics.r2_score(y_test,y_pred)], 'R2 Total': [metrics.r2_score(y,pred)],
         "RMSE Total":[np.sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(y,pred))], "RMSE Test":[np.sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test,y_pred))],
        "MAE Test":[mae_t], "MAE Total":[mae]}
    dfd = pd.DataFrame(data=d)
    dfd.set_index('Model', inplace=True)
    
   
    return pred,dfd,y_pred

def model_mix(pred_1,pred_2,pred_test_1,pred_test_2,X,y,date,model_name, perc_mod_1=0.7,perc_mod_2=0.3,measure=True, plots=True):
    '''
    plots = False by default: plot original data and predicted data
    By default it use 70% of the first model and 30% for the second one
    This function return the predicted values and a dataframe with error values
    '''
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.33, random_state=1)
    
    mix=perc_mod_1*pred_1+perc_mod_2*pred_2
    y_mix=perc_mod_1*pred_test_1+perc_mod_2*pred_test_2
    
    mae_t=mean_absolute_error(y_test,y_mix)
    mae=mean_absolute_error(y,mix)
    
    modello_mix = pd.DataFrame({"Actual": y, "Pred": mix})
    mod_mix=pd.concat([modello_mix, date], axis=1, join='inner')
    if plots== True:
        plot(mod_mix,label2=["Actual","Pred"],typ=4,model_name=model_name)
        
        print("R2 Test: ",metrics.r2_score(y_test,y_mix))
        print("RMSE Test: ",np.sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test,y_mix)))
        print("R2 Total: ",metrics.r2_score(y,mix))
        print("RMSE Total: ",np.sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(y,mix)))
        print("Test Mean Absolute Error: ",mae_t)
        print("Total Mean Absolute Error: ",mae)
    
    d = {"Model":[model_name],'R2 Test': [metrics.r2_score(y_test,y_mix)], 'R2 Total': [metrics.r2_score(y,mix)],
         "RMSE Total":[np.sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(y,mix))],"RMSE Test":[np.sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test,y_mix))],
        "MAE Test":[mae_t], "MAE Total":[mae]}
    dfd = pd.DataFrame(data=d)
    dfd.set_index('Model', inplace=True)
    
    return mix,dfd,y_mix

Introduction¶

The goal of this work is predicting the trend of seasonal influence based on the number of views of some wikipedia.it pages.
We used the Official data on influenza in Italy taken from "Influnet" coordinated by the Istituto Superiore di Sanità (ISS) with the support of the Ministry of Health. This network exists thanks to to the GPs, the PLS, the referents of the ASL and regions whose contribution is fundamental.
To grab all the informations about the views on wikipedia, we use this web tool including also web crawler and downloading data in the period between 01-07-2015 and 02-12-2018.
All the data used can be downloaded here.
For web automation downloads of CSV files we used Selenium packages

Part 2¶

Part 2.1 & 2.2¶

Find other Wikipedia pages related to flu whose pageview time series are correlated with the Influnet signal¶

To identify the pages we did the following steps:

  • We took from the page Influenza of Wikipedia all the links that refer to other pages
  • Data preprocessing
  • Using wordnet packages we compare "Influenza" with all the other words taken from the scraping $\rightarrow$ have been considered only the words with correlation $\ge$ 0.85
  • Add other words based on our personal intuition

#Preprocessing data
lista=list(scrape["Disease"])
deli=[x for x in lista if x.startswith('1') or x.startswith("Template") or x.startswith("Discussioni") or x.startswith("Collabora") or x.startswith("d:Q2840") or x.startswith("Digital object identifier") or x.startswith("q:") or x.startswith("wikt") or x.startswith('8') or x.startswith('978') or x.startswith('20') or x.startswith('5') or x.startswith('6') or x.startswith('Wiki') or x.startswith("Modifica") or x.startswith("Speciale") or x.startswith("Aiuto")]
parole=set(lista)-set(deli)
parole=[i for i in parole]
words=[]
for i in parole:
    words.append(re.sub(re.compile('la pagina non esiste'),'',i)) 

parole_final=[]  
for j in words:
    parole_final.append(re.sub(r'\([^)]*\)','',j))
parole_final.insert(0,"Influenza")
parole_final.sort()
In [25]:
influ = wn.synset('influenza.n.01')
similarity_list = {}
for i in parole_final:
    term_list = wn.synsets(i, lang = "ita")
    temp = [influ.wup_similarity(p) for p in term_list]
    if len(temp) != 0:
        try:
            if max(temp) >= 0.85:
                similarity_list.update({i: max(temp)})
        except:
            pass
simi = dict(sorted(similarity_list.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)[1:])
corr=[round(i,3) for i in simi.values()]
name=[i for i in simi.keys()]
simi=dict(zip(name,corr))
print("The most correlated words are: ", simi)

    correlazioni[parola]={"Word":parola,"Correlation":corre,"Path":path}
